# Project Name

A modern desktop application built with Electron, React, and TypeScript, leveraging the power of Vite for fast development and Electron Forge for seamless packaging and distribution.

## Tech Stack

- **[Electron](https://www.electronjs.org/)** - Cross-platform desktop application framework
- **[React](https://react.dev/)** - UI library for building interactive interfaces
- **[TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)** - Typed superset of JavaScript
- **[Vite](https://vitejs.dev/)** - Next-generation frontend build tool
- **[Electron Forge](https://www.electronforge.io/)** - Complete toolchain for building and distributing Electron apps

## Features

- ‚ö°Ô∏è Fast development with Vite's Hot Module Replacement (HMR)
- üé® Modern React 18 with hooks and functional components
- üîí Type-safe development with TypeScript
- üì¶ Easy packaging and distribution with Electron Forge
- üîß Pre-configured development environment
- üöÄ Production-ready build system

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- **Node.js** (v18 or higher)
- **npm** (v9 or higher) or **yarn**

## Getting Started

### Installation

Clone the repository and install dependencies:

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <your-repository-url>
cd <project-directory>

# Install dependencies
npm install
```

### Development

Start the development server with hot reload:

```bash
npm start
```

This will:
- Launch the Electron application
- Enable hot module replacement for React components
- Watch for file changes in both main and renderer processes
- Open DevTools automatically for debugging

### Building

Create a production build:

```bash
npm run package
```

This compiles your application and packages it for your current platform.

### Distribution

Create distributable installers:

```bash
npm run make
```

This will generate platform-specific distributables in the `out/make` directory:
- **Windows**: `.exe` installer
- **macOS**: `.dmg` disk image
- **Linux**: `.deb`, `.rpm`, or AppImage (depending on configuration)

### Publishing

Publish your application to distribution platforms:

```bash
npm run publish
```

> **Note**: Configure your publishing targets in `forge.config.ts` before running this command.

